From: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: share the throughput LED trigger across all bands

The throughput LED trigger is created per ieee80211_hw by
ieee80211_create_tpt_led_trigger(), which bails out with a WARN_ON() and
returns NULL if a trigger already exists for that hw.

Under the single-wiphy MLO model used by MT7996 every band registers its
own LED classdev (mt76-phy0/1/2) against the same hw via
mt76_register_phy() -> mt76_alloc_phy() -> mt76_led_init(), and the bands
can be initialised in any order (the extra bands actually come up before
the primary phy). The previous code created the trigger only for the
primary phy and let the others copy it, but since the primary initialises
last the secondary bands copied a NULL trigger and came up without one.

Create the trigger on whichever phy runs first, stash it on the primary
phy's classdev and let every band reuse it. This keeps create_tpt() to a
single call (no WARN_ON splat) and gives all of mt76-phy0/1/2 the same
throughput trigger regardless of init order.

Signed-off-by: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
---
 mac80211.c | 19 +++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/mac80211.c
+++ b/mac80211.c
@@ -217,11 +217,19 @@
 		 wiphy_name(hw->wiphy));
 
 	phy->leds.cdev.name = phy->leds.name;
-	phy->leds.cdev.default_trigger =
-		ieee80211_create_tpt_led_trigger(hw,
-					IEEE80211_TPT_LEDTRIG_FL_RADIO,
-					mt76_tpt_blink,
-					ARRAY_SIZE(mt76_tpt_blink));
+	/* The throughput LED trigger is created once per ieee80211_hw. Under
+	 * single-wiphy MLO every band registers its own LED classdev against
+	 * the same hw and the bands can initialise in any order, so create the
+	 * trigger on whichever phy runs first, stash it on the primary phy and
+	 * let every band reuse it. Calling ieee80211_create_tpt_led_trigger()
+	 * more than once trips a WARN_ON() and returns NULL. */
+	if (!dev->phy.leds.cdev.default_trigger)
+		dev->phy.leds.cdev.default_trigger =
+			ieee80211_create_tpt_led_trigger(hw,
+				IEEE80211_TPT_LEDTRIG_FL_RADIO,
+				mt76_tpt_blink,
+				ARRAY_SIZE(mt76_tpt_blink));
+	phy->leds.cdev.default_trigger = dev->phy.leds.cdev.default_trigger;
 
 	dev_info(dev->dev,
 		"registering led '%s'\n", phy->leds.name);
